  "prompt": "Why is my Kindle gift card not working on Amazon?",
  "response": "If your Kindle gift card isn't working on Amazon, it could be due to several reasons. Here are some common issues and solutions:\n\n1. **Incorrect Redemption**:\n   - Ensure you're redeeming the gift card on the correct Amazon website (e.g., Amazon.com for U.S. customers, Amazon.co.uk for UK customers, etc.).\n   - Double-check that you entered the code correctly, including hyphens.\n\n2. **Expired or Invalid Card**:\n   - Check the expiration date on the gift card. If it\u2019s expired, it won\u2019t work.\n   - Verify that the card was purchased from an authorized retailer and hasn\u2019t been tampered with.\n\n3. **Already Redeemed**:\n   - If someone else has already used the code, it won\u2019t work. Ensure the card was kept secure and not shared with others.\n\n4. **Region Restrictions**:\n   - Kindle gift cards are often region-specific. If you\u2019re trying to use a card from one country on a different country\u2019s Amazon site, it may not work.\n\n5. **Account Issues**:\n   - Ensure you\u2019re logged into the correct Amazon account.\n   - Check if your account has any restrictions or issues that might prevent the redemption.\n\n6. **Usage Restrictions**:\n   - Kindle gift cards can only be used to purchase Kindle books, apps, games, and other eligible digital content. They cannot be used for physical products or subscriptions like Audible.\n\n7. **Technical Glitch**:\n   - Try redeeming the card on a different device or browser.\n   - Clear your browser\u2019s cache and cookies, then attempt again.\n\n8. **Contact Customer Support**:\n   - If none of the above solutions work, contact Amazon Customer Service with the gift card details (code, purchase receipt, etc.) for assistance.\n\nTo redeem the gift card:\n- Go to **Your Account** > **Gift cards** > **Redeem a Gift Card**.\n- Enter the code and click **Apply to Your Balance**.\n\nIf you\u2019re still having trouble, Amazon\u2019s customer support team can investigate and resolve the issue.",
